Package software.kes.kraftwerk.constraints

Class BigIntegerRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • software.kes.kraftwerk.constraints.BigIntegerRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.math.BigInteger>, Constraint<java.math.BigInteger>
    public final class BigIntegerRange
extends java.lang.Object
implements Constraint<java.math.BigInteger>, java.lang.Iterable<java.math.BigInteger>
    A range of BigIntegers. Like all ranges, it is immutable and its span always includes a minimum of one value.

    Construct using one of the static methods (inclusive(java.math.BigInteger, java.math.BigInteger), exclusive(java.math.BigInteger, java.math.BigInteger)),

    or by using from(java.math.BigInteger): 

     BigIntegerRange.from(BigInteger.ZERO).to(BigInteger.TWO)      // 0..2 inclusive
 BigIntegerRange.from(BigInteger.ZERO).until(BigInteger.TWO)   // 0..2 exclusive

      • from

        public static BigIntegerRange.BigIntegerRangeFrom from​(java.math.BigInteger minInclusive)
        Partially constructs a BigIntegerRange with its lower bound.

        With the result, you can call to or until with the upper bound to create the BigIntegerRange.

        Parameters:
        minInclusive - the lower bound (inclusive) of the range
